author: Chad
description:
I plan on using this on a SL1 run I want to do.

- During early-game, use Raw Broadsword with any buffs necesary.

- Use Lloyd's Sword Ring until you get Dragonslayer's Axe and Prisoner's Chain. From that point on, those two items will help you out WAY more than Lloyd's Sword Ring.

- ALWAYS be on full health. Unless you're in full health with Lloyd's Shield Ring on, you're gonna get one-shotted from ANY boss.

- Don't waste time with Yoel. This is a SL1 run, levels you gain through "drawing out true strength" also count.

Good luck.
title: Chad's SL1

author: Anonymous
description:
One-shot build using lightning storm at point blank.
inspired by a YT video.
When you find the host, use the sunlight straight sword WA, then cast tears (WA cancels tears if cast afterwards)
Using Vordt's perseverance (2 handed you have the STR) right before you go in, immediately swap to the morrion blade, and run up to the host at point blank and cast LS, and if the host is right next to you, you should manage 2k damage, which should one-shot just about anyone.

The armor is optional, but be aware that you have next to no VIT, and you need at least SOMETHING in every slot, for the defense.

You can swap LS for Wrath of the Gods, just switch the lightning clutch to a sage ring.
title: Lightning Hypermode
